  "prompt": "Who invented Classical music?",
  "response": "Classical music was not invented by a single individual; rather, it evolved over several centuries with contributions from many composers and musicians. The term \"Classical music\" generally refers to a tradition of Western art music that spans from approximately the 11th century to the present, with a focus on music composed from roughly 1750 to 1820, known as the Classical period.\n\nDuring the Classical period, key figures included composers like Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, Ludwig van Beethoven, and Joseph Haydn, who developed and refined many of the forms and styles associated with this era, such as the symphony, sonata, and string quartet.\n\nThus, Classical music is the result of a long historical process and the collective efforts of many individuals, rather than a single invention by one person.",
